items.title: An Unwelcome Fight Over Obeying Court Orders
items.description: Even the righteous cause of deporting brutal Venezuelan gangs should not tempt the executive branch to undermine the legitimate role of courts.

items.title: We Must Restore the U.S. Agency for Global Media, Not Eliminate It
items.description: Repressive regimes have failed to block the agency’s promotion of freedom around the world. Doing so ourselves could have drastic consequences.

items.title: Why Trump Doesn’t Want Judicial Review of His Deportation of Venezuelans
items.description: The president’s legal position that he can proceed with no input from Congress or judicial review is on shaky ground.

items.title: The Visitor Mocks the Illegal-Immigration Craze
items.description: Bruce LaBruce outstrips his contemporary political-film allies.

items.title: Milei Isn’t Out of the Woods Yet
items.description: Milei has not yet been able to rid Argentina of its maze of capital controls, despite his promises to do so.
